alluxio.client.file

Interface FileSystem

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseFileSystem, LineageFileSystem

    @PublicApi
public interface FileSystem
    Basic file system interface supporting metadata operations and data operations. Developers should not implement this class but extend the default implementation provided by BaseFileSystem instead. This ensures any new methods added to the interface will be provided by the default implementation.

      • mount

        void mount(AlluxioURI alluxioPath,
           AlluxioURI ufsPath,
           MountOptions options)
    throws IOException,
           AlluxioException
        Mounts a UFS subtree to the given Alluxio path. The Alluxio path is expected not to exist as the method creates it. If the path already exists, a AlluxioException will be thrown. This method does not transfer any data or metadata from the UFS. It simply establishes the connection between the given Alluxio path and UFS path.
        Parameters:
        alluxioPath - an Alluxio path to mount the data to
        ufsPath - a UFS path to mount the data from
        options - options to associate with this operation
        Throws:
        IOException - if a non-Alluxio exception occurs
        AlluxioException - if an Alluxio exception occurs

      • unmount

        void unmount(AlluxioURI path,
             UnmountOptions options)
      throws IOException,
             AlluxioException
        Unmounts a UFS subtree identified by the given Alluxio path. The Alluxio path match a previously mounted path. The contents of the subtree rooted at this path are removed from Alluxio but the corresponding UFS subtree is left untouched.
        Parameters:
        path - an Alluxio path, this must be a mount point
        options - options to associate with this operation
        Throws:
        IOException - if a non-Alluxio exception occurs
        AlluxioException - if an Alluxio exception occurs
